description: Agilent Technologies provides bio-analytical and electronic measurement solutions to the communications, electronics, life sciences and chemical analysis industries.
American Superconductor provides power electronics for wind turbines and power grids.
Ameriprise provides financial planning, annuities, wealth, and asset management services.
Amgen develops, manufactures and markets medicines for serious illnesses.

Affiliated Managers Group is a global asset management company with equity investments in boutique investment management firms, which maintain operational autonomy, and receive assistance from the company in marketing and distribution.
AMETEK makes electronic instruments and electromechanical devices for the aerospace and defense, medical, mass transit, petrochemical, power and other industrial markets.

AMD is a semiconductor company that primarily offers x86 microprocessors as standalone central processing units (CPU) or incorporated into accelerated processing units (APU), chipsets and discrete graphics processing units (GPUs) for the consumer, commercial and professional graphics markets.
AMC Networks owns and operates TV programming channels including AMC, WE tv, BBC AMERICA, IFC and Sundance, in the U.S. and internationally.
Ambac provides financial guarantees, such as credit derivative contracts, and other financial services to clients in the public and private sectors.
Applied provides manufacturing equipment, services and software to the semiconductor, display, and solar photovoltaic industries.

Alexion is a pharmaceutical company focused on ultra-rare life-threatening genetic disorders. Company products include Soliris, a therapeutic approved for paroxysmal nocturnal hemoglobinuria (PNH) and for atypical hemolytic uremic syndrome (aHUS); Strensiq for the treatment of Hypophosphatasia (HPP); and Kanuma for the treatment of Lysosomal Acid Lipase Deficiency (LAL-D).

Acquired by Intel in 2015, Altera was a global semiconductor company providing field-programmable gate array (FPGA) products to the telecom, wireless, industrial automation, military, auto, and other markets.

Allegion offers mechanical and electronic security products, such as steel doors and door frames, electronic and biometric access control systems, locks and key systems. Company brands include Falcon, LCN, Kryptonite, and Schlage.
Allstate provides property-liability and life insurance in the U.S. and Canada.
The company operates Alaska Airlines and Horizon Air, serving a route network spanning North America.

Align designs, manufactures and markets the Invisalign System for tooth alignment therapy. The company also makes iTero oral scanners, and provides computer-aided design and manufacturing digital services used in dentistry, orthodontics, and dental records storage.

Zoetis developes, manufactures and commercializes animal medicines and vaccines. The company had been a business unit of Pfizer for more than 60 years, prior to becoming an independent public company in 2013.

Zions provides community banking services, including business banking, commercial and residential development, construction and term lending, retail banking, residential mortgage servicing and lending, and trust and wealth management. The company operates primarily in the West and Southwest of the U.S.

Zimmer Biomet designs, manufactures and markets orthopaedic reconstructive products; sports medicine, biologics, extremities and trauma products; spine, bone healing, craniomaxillofacial and thoracic products; dental implants; and related surgical products.
YUM develops, operates, franchises and licenses KFC, Pizza Hut and Taco Bell restaurants worldwide.
Acquired by Verizon, Yahoo! generates revenue from display and search advertising on Yahoo! online properties and third-party websites.
Xylem designs and manufactures equipment, and provides services, for water and wastewater applications, such as filtration and treatment.

Acquired by Exxon Mobil in 2009, XTO Energy was engaged in exploration, development, and exploitation of oil and gas properties, and in the production, processing, marketing and transportation of oil and gas.

Xerox primarily provides business process outsourcing services, including customer care, transaction processing, finance and accounting, and human resources, and document outsourcing services, such as workflow automation and centralized print services.
DENTSPLY designs, manufactures and markets consumable dental products for the professional dental market around the world.
Exxon Mobil explores for and produces crude oil and natural gas,  and manufactures and markets petroleum products and commodity petrochemicals.
Xilinx designs and develops programmable integrated circuits.
XL Group provides property and casualty insurance and reinsurance to industrial, commercial and professional firms, insurance companies and other enterprises.
Xcel Energy is a holding company whose utility subsidiaries provide electricity and natural gas in Minnesota, Wisconsin, Colorado, Michigan, New Mexico, North and South Dakota, and Texas.
Cimarex Energy is an oil and gas exploration and production company, operating mainly in Oklahoma, Texas and New Mexico.
U. S. Steel produces flat-rolled and tubular steel products from iron ore and coke, in North America and Europe.
Wynn Resorts develops, owns and operates destination casino resorts that integrate hotel accommodations with dining outlets, premium retail, entertainment theaters and meeting complexes.
Wyndham Destinations is a vacation ownership and exchange company with presence in over 100 countries.
Acquired by Pfizer in 2009, Wyeth engaged in the discovery, development, manufacture, distribution and sale of pharmaceutical, consumer healthcare, and animal health products.
Weyerhaeuser grows and harvests trees, and manufactures and sells building products, pulp and paper.
Acquired by Mars, Incorporated in 2008, The Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company manufactured and marketed chewing gum and other confectionery products worldwide.

Western Union provides global money movement and payment services, primarily consumer-to-consumer money transfers, as well as consumer-to-business bill payments. The company also provides foreign exchange and cross-border, cross-currency transaction services for businesses and individuals.
WestRock manufactures containerboard and paperboard, and makes packaging solutions.
WPX is an oil and gas exploration and production company engaged in the exploitation of long-life unconventional properties in North Dakota and in the southwestern U.S..
Wal-Mart operates retail stores, warehouse clubs and e-commerce websites around the world. The company strategy is to lead on price.
Williams is primarily a U.S. based operator of interstate gas pipelines, and provider of natural gas and natural gas liquids gathering, treatment, processing and compression services.
Washington Mutual filed for bankruptcy in 2008. Prior to the bankruptcy, the company had been a consumer and small business banking company in the U.S.
Waste Management provides waste collection, transfer, recycling and disposal services in North America. The company owns a number of landfill sites and landfill gas-to-energy facilities.
Willis Towers Watson provides property and liability insurance brokerage services, reinsurance, and employee benefits brokerage and consulting services.

Windstream provides broadband communications, voice and digital television to consumers in the U.S., as well as data, cloud solutions, unified communications and managed services to small business and enterprise clients.

Winmark franchises value-oriented retail store concepts that buy, sell and trade used merchandise, such as used clothing and accessories, toys, sporting goods, or musical instruments, in the U.S. and Canada.

Whirlpool manufactures and markets major home appliances, such as refrigerators, cooking stoves, dishwashers, and 
laundry machines under brand names such as Whirlpool, KitchenAid, and Maytag.
Weatherford provides equipment and services used in the drilling, evaluation, completion, production and intervention of oil and gas wells.
Acquired by Amazon in 2017, Whole Foods operated natural and organic foods supermarkets in the U.S., Canada, and the U.K.

Wells Fargo provides retail, commercial and corporate banking across the U.S., as well as wholesale banking, mortgage banking, equipment leasing, securities brokerage, investment banking, and other financial services.
Wendy’s owns and franchises Wendy’s restaurants in the U.S..
Welltower is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns properties in the U.S., Canada and the U.K., consisting of seniors housing and post-acute communities and outpatient medical facilities.

WEC Energy Group is a holding company, whose subsidiaries provide regulated natural gas and electricity, as well as nonregulated renewable energy primarily in Wisconsin, Illinois, and other Midwestern states of the U.S.
Waddell & Reed provides investment management, advisory, underwriting and distribution for mutual funds and institutional and separately managed accounts.
Western Digital makes data storage solutions such as hard disk drives and solid-state drives

Walgreens Boots Alliance operates retail pharmacies across the U.S. and Europe under brands including Walgreens, Duane Reade, Boots and Alliance Healthcare. The company also operates a global pharmaceutical wholesale and distribution network, and a portfolio of
Acquired by Wells Fargo in 2008, Wachovia provided commercial and retail banking and trust services.

Waters designs, manufactures, sells and services liquid chromatography, mass spectrometry, thermal analysis, rheometry and calorimetry analytical instruments, related software, and consumables. These products are used by life sciences, biochemical, industrial, nutritional safety, environmental, academic and governmental customers.
Prior to its merger with Alliance Boots in 2014, Walgreen primarily operated drugstores and specialty pharmacies in the U.S.

Verizon provides wireless voice and data communications, wireline broadband video and data for consumers in the U.S. The company offers corporate networking solutions, data center and cloud services to business and government customers in the U.S. and abroad.
Ventas is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns a portfolio of seniors housing and healthcare properties located in the U.S., Canada and the U.K.
Vertex Pharmaceuticals discovers, develops, manufactures and commercializes therapies for the treatment of cystic fibrosis, including ORKAMBI and KALYDECO.
VeriSign provides Internet domain name registry and Internet security services.

Verisk Analytics provides data analytics services to insurance, natural resources, healthcare, financial services, government, and risk management customers. The company collects and analyzes billions of data records to provide decision making information integrated into customer workflows.
Vornado is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns office space and residential properties, primarily in New York City and Washington D.C.
Vulcan is a U.S. based producer of crushed stone, sand and gravel used in construction, and of asphalt mix and ready-mixed concrete.

Valero operates petroleum refineries in the U.S., Canada, and the U.K., and markets refined products through Valero-branded gas stations and on a wholesale basis. The company also operates ethanol plants in the central plains region of the U.S.

Meridian develops, manufactures, sells and distributes disease diagnostic test kits, bulk antigens, antibodies, and bioresearch reagents, and performs contract development and manufacture of proteins and other biologicals for use by biopharmaceutical and biotechnology companies engaged in research for new drugs and vaccines.

Viavi, formerly JDS Uniphase Corporation, is a provider of network equipment and optical products for telecommunications service providers, equipment manufacturers and enterprises. The company also provides anti-counterfeiting solutions for currency authentication, and optical instruments for security, safety, and other applications.
Viacom creates TV programs, films, entertainment applications, games, and consumer products. Company media brands include Nickelodeon, Comedy Central, BET, and Paramount Pictures.

Varian Medical Systems makes medical devices and software for treating cancer and other conditions with radiotherapy, radiosurgery, proton therapy and brachytherapy. The company also makes X-ray imaging components for medical, scientific, cargo screening, and industrial applications.

U.S. Bancorp is a bank holding company that provides lending and depository services, cash management, capital markets, trust and investment management, as well as credit card services, merchant and ATM processing, mortgage banking, insurance, brokerage and leasing.
The company rents construction and industrial equipment, aerial work platforms, trench safety equipment, power and HVAC equipment, pumps, and general tools and light equipment in the U.S. and Canada.

Visa is a global payments technology company that operates a payment processing network, which facilitates authorization, clearing and settlement of payment transactions, and provides fraud protection for account holders. Visa does not issue cards, extend credit or set rates for account holders. In most cases, account holder and merchant relationships are managed by Visa's financial institution clients.
Acquired by Altria Group in 2008, UST was engaged in manufacturing and marketing of smokeless tobacco products and wine.

Urban Outfitters is a retail and wholesale apparel, accessories, and home goods company, operating under the Urban Outfitters, Anthropologie, Free People, Terrain and Bhldn brands. Company retails stores are primarily located in the U.S., Canada, and Western Europe.

United Technologies is a diversified technology company. Its products include Otis elevators and escalators; building heating, ventilating, air conditioning and refrigeration systems; Pratt & Whitney aircraft engines and other aerospace products and services sold to aircraft manufacturers, airlines and governments.

United Parcel Service is a package delivery company that was founded in 1907. The company delivers packages in over 200 countries and provides logistics services, such as distribution, customs brokerage and insurance.
VF designs, produces, markets and distributes branded apparel and footwear. Company brands include The North Face, Vans, Timberland, Wrangler, Lee, Nautica, Majestic and Kipling.
Union Pacific provides railroad transportation in the western two-thirds of the U.S., primarily transporting agricultural, automotive, chemical, and industrial products and coal.
Unum provides life and disability insurance in the U.S. and the U.K.
UnitedHealth provides employer, individual, Medicare, and other health insurance plans.
Ulta Beauty is a beauty retailer in the U.S. that offers cosmetics, fragrances, skin and hair care products, and salon services.
Unisys provides information technology services to enterprises and governments. Offerngs include cloud and IT infrastructure, application services, security solutions and server technology.
The company owns and operates acute care hospitals, behavioral health centers, surgical hospitals, ambulatory surgery centers and radiation oncology centers, primarily in the U.S. and the U.K.
United-Guardian manufactures and markets cosmetic ingredients, personal care and health care products, pharmaceuticals, medical lubricants, and specialty industrial products.
UDR is a real estate investment trust (REIT) that develops, owns, and operates multifamily apartment communities throughout the U.S.

The company is a holding company parent of United Airlines, transporting people and cargo through a global route network with hubs at Newark Liberty, Chicago O’Hare, Denver, George Bush Houston, Los Angeles, A.B. Won Pat Guam, San Francisco and Washington Dulles International airports.
Under Armour developes, markets and distributes branded athletic apparel, footwear and accessories. The company primarily sells its products on a wholesale basis to retailers.
Acquired by Johnson Controls in 2016, Tyco provided security products and services, fire detection and suppression products, and life safety products.

Textron is a diversified company that manufactures, sells, and services Beechcraft, Cessna, and Hawker aircraft, Bell helicopters, unmanned aircraft systems and weapons, and fuel systems and automotive components. The company also provides financing to purchasers of its aircraft and helicopters
TI designs and makes semiconductors that it sells to electronics manufacturers around the world. Products include analog semiconductors, digital signal processors, microcontrollers.

Time Warner is a media and entertainment company that operates a cable TV network and digital media properties, provides Home Box Office (HBO) premium pay television and streaming services, and owns Warner Bros. film, home video and videogame production and distribution.
Twitter provides products that enable people to share information through mobile devices and personal computers. The company derives revenue from advertising and data licensing.

Time Warner Cable provides video, high-speed data and voice services over cable systems located primarily in New York State, including New York City, the Carolinas, the Midwest, Southern California, including Los Angeles, and Texas.

Acquired by Ingersoll-Rand in 2007, Trane manufactured commercial and residential heating, ventilation and air conditioning equipment. Trane through its predecessors had been in the HVAC business since 1864.
The company provides global payment solutions, such as processing services and acquiring solutions to merchants, and  general purpose reloadable prepaid and payroll cards.

Tyson Foods is a food company with brands such as Tyson, Jimmy Dean, Hillshire Farm, Sara Lee,  Ball Park, Wright, Aidells and State Fair. The company produces chicken, beef, pork as well as prepared foods.
Tesla designs, manufactures and sells fully electric vehicles and energy storage products. The company operates its own global network of vehicle sales and service centers.
Tractor Supply Company operates retail stores in rural communities of the U.S., supplying recreational farmers, ranchers, tradesmen and small businesses.

The Travelers Companies is a holding company that provides a wide range of commercial and personal property and casualty insurance products and services to businesses, government units, associations and individuals.
T. Rowe Price provides global investment management services to individual and institutional investors in mutual funds, separately managed accounts, and other sponsored investment portfolios

TripAdvisor is an online travel company. TripAdvisor aggregates travelers’ reviews and opinions about destinations, accommodations, and activities, and allows users to book hotels, vacation rentals, flights, activities, and restaurants.
Tapestry designs and markets luxury consumer products under Coach, Kate Spade New York, and Stuart Weitzman brands.
Thermo Fisher provides scientific instruments and laboratory equipment, software, and consumables to biotech companies, hospitals and diagnostic labs, research institutions and government agencies.
Torchmark is an insurance holding company that provides individual life and supplemental health insurance products.
Tellabs provides optical and packet-switched network equipment to network service providers.
The Timken Company was founded in 1899. Timken engineers, manufactures and markets bearings, transmissions, gearboxes, belts, chain and related products repair services around the world.
TJX Companies is a discount apparel and home fashion retailer, operating stores under the T.J. Maxx, Marshalls, HomeGoods, and other names.
Acquired by International Paper in 2012, Temple-Inland manufactured corrugated packaging and building products.
Tiffany's was founded in 1837, and primarily operates jewelry retail stores around the world.
Titanium Metals produces titanium melted and mill products, and recycles titanium scrap.
Tenet operates hospitals, short-stay surgical hospitals, and outpatient centers primarily in the U.S.
Target is a U.S. general merchandise and food retaier

TEGNA, formerly Gannett Co., Inc., operates in two business segments: the Media Segment, which includes a number of television stations, and the Digital Segment, which primarily consists of the Cars.com and CareerBuilder businesses.
Terex makes cranes, lifts, towers, materials processing equipment such as crushers, and construction equipment such as backhoes, excavators and
Teradyne makes automatic test systems used to test electronics systems in the consumer electronics, wireless, automotive, industrial, computing, communications, and aerospace and defense industries.
TE Connectivity manufacturers electrical components, such as connector, sensors, and relays for transportation, industrial and communications markets.

Acquired by Wisconsin Energy in 2015, Integrys Energy Group was a holding company for regulated utility and non-regulated subsidiaries providing natural gas and electricity in the Mid-West of the U.S.
Acquired by Emera in 2016, TECO Energy was a holding company for regulated utilities providing electricity in Florida and New Mexico.

TransDigm designs, produces and supplies proprietary components for use on commercial and military aircraft. Company products include mechanical/electro-mechanical actuators and controls, ignition systems and engine technology, pumps and valves, power conditioning devices, AC/DC electric motors and generators, batteries and chargers, latching and locking devices, cockpit security systems, and aircraft audio systems.
Teradata provides software, hardware, and consulting services for enterprise data warehousing, integration, and business intelligence.

The company is a beer brewer with a portfolio of brands that includes Carling, Coors Light, Molson Canadian and Staropramen. 
Molson and Coors were founded in 1786 and 1873, respectively.

AT&T provides wireless communications, broadband Internet, digital video services, and local and long-distance telephone services to consumers in the U.S., Mexico and Latin America and to businesses worldwide.
Sysco is a North American distributor of food and related products to restaurants, healthcare and educational facilities, lodging establishments and other foodservice customers.

Acquired by Atos in 2018, Syntel provided digital transformation, information technology and knowledge process outsourcing services to enterprises in the Banking and Financial Services, Healthcare and Life Sciences, Insurance, and other industries.
Symantec provides online security products to consumers and enterprises.

Stryker is a medical technology company. Its products include implants used in joint replacement and trauma surgeries; surgical equipment and surgical navigation systems; endoscopic and communications systems; patient handling equipment; and neurosurgical, neurovascular and spinal devices.
Synchrony offers consumer credit products, such as private label credit cards, through retailer and manufacturer partners such as Lowe’s, Walmart, Amazon and Ethan Allen.
Southwestern is an oil and gas exploration and production company operating predominantly in the U.S.
Skyworks makes analog semiconductors for the automotive, communications, industrial, medical, and military applications.

The company is a diversified global provider of hand tools, power tools and accessories, mechanical access solutions such as automatic doors and commercial locking systems, electronic security and monitoring systems, healthcare solutions, and other products and services for industrial applications.

Acquired in 2018, SUPERVALU was a successor to two firms established in the 1870s. Supervalu was a wholesale grocery distributor to independent retail customers in the U.S., and a discount grocery retailer under the Save-A-Lot store name.
SunEdison filed for Chapter 11 bankruptcy in 2016. Prior to bankruptcy, the company developed photovoltaic energy solutions, and owned and operated solar power plants
Acquired by Energy Transfer Partners, L.P. in 2012, Sunoco was principally a petroleum refiner and marketer, and chemicals manufacturer
Constellation Brands sells alcoholic beverages, including beer, wine, and spirits in the U.S. and Canada.
Seagate provides hard disk drives and other electronic data storage products including solid state hybrid drives, solid state drives, PCIe cards and SATA controllers.

The company conducts its business primarily through State Street Bank, which traces its beginnings to the founding of the Union Bank in 1792. State Street Bank operates as a specialized bank, referred to as a trust or custody bank, that services and manages assets on behalf of its institutional clients, which include mutual funds, collective investment funds and other investment pools, corporate and public retirement plans, insurance comp
Questar develops and produces natural gas, operates interstate gas pipelines and storage facilities, and provides retail natural gas distribution in Utah, Wyoming and Idaho.

Acquired by Abbott Laboratories in 2017, St. Jude Medical developed, manufactured and distributed cardiovascular medical devices for cardiac rhythm management and cardiovascular and atrial fibrillation therapy, and interventional pain therapy and neurostimulation devices for the management of chronic pain and movement disorders.
SunTrust Banks provides consumer banking, private wealth management, wholesale and mortgage banking services in the South-Eastern and Mid-Atlantic regions of the U.S.
Scripps serves audiences and businesses through a portfolio of TV, radio and digital media brands, as well as local and national digital journalism and information businesses
Sempra Energy is a holding company for regulated utilities that provide electricity and gas in Southern California.

Stericycle provides collection, processing, and disposal services for regulated and specialized waste, such as medical, pharmaceutical, or hazardous waste, and secure destruction of documents and e-media. The company has worldwide processing and service facilities, and transfer sites.
Acquired in 2017, Staples sold office supplies, business technology products, facilities supplies, copy and print services, and office furniture through retail stores, direct sales, and online.
S&P Global provides ratings, benchmarks, analytics and data to the capital and commodity markets worldwide.
Simon is a self-administered and self-managed real estate investment trust (REIT) that owns, develops and manages retail mail real estate properties.

Acquired by Santander in 2008, Sovereign Bank was a savings bank attracting deposits from a network of community banking offices, and originating small business and middle market commercial loans, multi-family loans, residential mortgage loans, home equity loans and lines of credit, and auto and other consumer loans in the communities served by those offices.
Southern Company owns public utilities supplying electricity in Alabama, Georgia, Florida, and Mississippi.
Synopsys provides electronic design automation software and pre-designed circuits to customers who design and test integrated circuits.

Scripps developers lifestyle-oriented content for television and internet, including HGTV, Food Network, Travel Channel, DIY Network, Cooking Channel and Great American Country TV networks in the U.S.
Acquired by Western Digital in 2015, SanDisk was a supplier of NAND flash storage card products.

Snap-on manufactures and markets hand and power tools, tool storage, diagnostics software, information and management systems, shop equipment and other solutions for vehicle dealerships and repair centers, as well as for other industrial customers.

SLM Corporation, commonly known as Sallie Mae, is a federally chartered government sponsored enterprise, with the goal of furthering access to higher education by providing liquidity to the education loan marketplace. The company originates and services private education Loans.
SL Green is real estate investment trust (REIT) that develops and manages office properties in the New York Metropolitan area.
Founded in 1926, Schlumberger is a supplier of technology, project management and information solutions to the oil and gas exploration and production industry.

Smucker’s was established in 1897. The company manufactures and markets branded coffee, pet food, peanut butter, fruit spreads, shortening and oils, baking mixes and ready-to-spread frostings, frozen sandwiches, flour and baking ingredients, juices and beverages worldwide.
SITE Centers Corp. (formerly DDR Corp.) is a Real Estate Investment Trust (REIT) in the business of acquiring, owning, developing, and managing shopping centers.
Acquired by Schlumberger in 2010, Smith International provided products and services used during the drilling, completion and production phases of oil and gas exploration and development.
Signet is a U.S. and U.K. retailer of diamond jewelry, operating retail stores in shopping malls and off-mall locations, under brand names including Kay Jewelers and Zales Jewelers.

Acquired by the German drug company Merck KGaA in 2014, Sigma-Aldrich developed, manufactured, and distributed a broad range of chemicals, biochemicals and equipment used in scientific research, pharmaceutical development and other high technology manufacturing.
Sherwin-Williams, founded in 1866, develops, manufactures, and sells paint and coatings to industrial, commercial and retail customers primarily in North and South America.
The company operated Kmart and Sears retail stores in the U.S. prior to its bankruptcy and asset sale.
Prior to its 2009 merger with Merck, Schering-Plough was a global biopharmaceutical company.

Sealed Air provides food packaging products, such as vacuum shrink bags, flexible films, absorbent materials and trays; facility cleaning and hygiene solutions; and protective and specialty packaging such as Bubble Wrap packaging.

Spectra Energy gathers, processes, transmits over its pipelines, stores, and distributes natural gas in the U.S. and Canada, 
and also owns and operates a crude oil pipeline system.
Charles Schwab is a savings and loan holding company that engages in wealth management, securities brokerage, banking, custody, and financial advisory services.

Acquired by Dominion Energy in 2019, SCANA was a holding company whose wholly-owned regulated utility subsidiaries provided electricity and natural gas to retail and wholesale customers in North and South Carolina.
Starbucks is a global coffee roaster, marketer and retailer.

Acquired by Motorola in 2006, Symbol designed and manufactured enterprise mobility solutions such as data capture products, mobile computing platforms and software management tools, wireless infrastructure, and radio frequency identification tags.
SBA Communications is a REIT that owns, operates, and leases antenna towers and other structures used for wireless communications.
Acquired by the Publicis Groupe in 2015, Sapient offered marketing strategy, web design and development, and advertising services.

Sanmina provides product design, manufacturing, and logistics services to original equipment manufacturers in the communications networks, storage, industrial, defense and aerospace, medical, energy and other industries.
The Boston Beer Company is a U.S. brewer of beers under the Samuel Adams and other brands, and of flavored malt, hard cider and other beverages.

Acquired in 2008 by the Liberty Mutual Insurance Company, Safeco Corporation was an insurance holding company that provided property and casualty insurance to individuals and small- to mid-size businesses in the U.S.
Sprint offers wireless and wireline communications products and services to consumer, business, and government subscribers in the U.S.
Acquired in 2010, IMS Health was a global provider of market intelligence to the pharmaceutical and healthcare industries.

Raytheon is a defense company. Its offerings include air and missile defense systems, radars, and naval electronic systems for the U.S. Department of Defense and other government customers; technical and professional services for the intelligence, defense, and commercial customers; and missile and combat systems for the U.S. and allied armed forces.
Prior to its 2015 bankruptcy, RadioShack was a consumer electronics retailer.
Republic provide non-hazardous solid waste collection, transfer, disposal, and recycling in the U.S.
RR Donnelley is an advertising and customer communications company that produces magazines, catalogs, retail inserts, directories, statements, packaging, and direct mail for its clients.
Range Resources is a natural gas and oil company that explores and developes natural gas and oil properties in the Appalachian region of the U.S.
Ross Stores operates retail apparel and home fashion stores for price-conscious shoppers.

Roper is a diversified technology company that provides diagnostic and laboratory software to healthcare providers, devices for computer-assisted surgery, digital imaging products for scientific and industrial use, radio frequency identification products for toll and traffic systems and access card readers, and fluid handling and materials analysis equipment.
Rockwell Automation provides industrial automation products, such as industrial control panels, machine control systems, sensors and switches.
Acquired by the Dow Chemical Company in 2008, Rohm and Haas was a specialty materials company manufacturing electronic materials, paint and coatings, and packaging and building materials.

ResMed makes medical devices and software applications that diagnose, treat and manage respiratory disorders including sleep disordered breathing, chronic obstructive pulmonary disease, neuromuscular disease and other chronic diseases.
Ralph Lauren designs, markets, and distributes apparel, accessories, and home furnishings through department stores and owned retail stores.

Raymond James Financial is a financial services company engaged in the underwriting, distribution, trading and brokerage of equity and debt securities and the sale of mutual funds and other investment products.

Transocean provides offshore contract drilling services for oil and gas wells. The company operates a fleet of midwater, deepwater, ultra-deepwater, and harsh environment floaters, jackups, and drillships.
Red Hat provides open source software consulting and support services, typically under annual or multi-year subscriptions.
Robert Half International provides specialized staffing, such as temporary, full-time, and project professionals in the fields of accounting and finance.

Regions Financial is a financial holding company that provides traditional commercial, retail and mortgage banking, as well as asset management, securities brokerage, insurance brokerage, and other financial services.

Regeneron Pharmaceuticals is a biopharmaceutical company that discovers, develops, manufactures, and commercializes medicines for the treatment of eye diseases, LDL cholesterol, and other medical conditions.
Regency Centers is a REIT that owns direct or partial interests in grocery-anchored community and neighborhood shopping centers.
Everest underwrites reinsurance and insurance in the U.S. and international markets.
Acquired in 2019, Rowan provided offshore contract drilling services to the oil and gas industry, with its fleet of jack-up rigs and ultra-deepwater drillships.
Royal Caribbean operates cruise ships with worldwide vacation itineraries.

Raven is a diversified technology company serving the industrial, agricultural, energy, construction, and defense markets. The major products of the company are precision agriculture tools, such as field computers, GPS-guidance steering systems and planter controls; plastic films and sheeting; and high-altitude balloons, tethered aerostats, and radar processing systems.

LiveRamp Holdings provides consumer data to marketers. The data includes demographic, socio-economic, and lifestyle information, as well as individual- and household-level identifiers that help target online and offline advertising.
Acquired by British American Tobacco in 2017, Reynolds American was a U.S. tobacco company that manufactured cigarettes, smokeless tobacco products, and digital vapor cigarettes.
Rite Aid is a U.S. retail drugstore chain.

Ryder offers transportation and supply chain management solutions. The company provides customers with trucks and maintenance services, while its customers provide their own drivers and exercise control over the vehicles. Ryder also offers comprehensive distribution and transportation services.

Qorvo makes radio frequency semiconductors for broadband data connectivity, used in smartphones, tablets, wearables, broadband customer premise equipment, home automation, in-vehicle infotainment, data center and military radar and communications.

Acquired by Cavium in 2016, QLogic provided fibre channel, high-speed ethernet and converged network adapters and application-specific integrated circuits (ASICs) for rack and tower and bladed servers and storage systems.

Qualcomm makes integrated circuits and system software based on CDMA, OFDMA and other technologies for use in voice and data communications, application processing, multimedia and global positioning system products. The company also licenses its intellectual property to manufacturers of mobile devices and infrastructure equipment.
Acquired by CenturyLink in 2010, Quest provided local and long-distance communications, network access, wireless and video services to residential, business, governmental and wholesale customers.
PayPal provides a technology platform for digital and mobile payments for consumers and merchants worldwide.
Pioneer is an oil and gas exploration and production company operating primarily in Texas and Colorado.

Prior to its merger with Linde in 2018, Praxair supplied atmospheric gases such as oxygen, nitrogen and argon, and process gases such as carbon dioxide, helium, hydrogen and acetylene, for industrial use.

Quanta provides specialty contracting services to the electric power and oil and gas industries. Services include design, installation and maintenance of electric power transmission infrastructure, substation facilities, pipelines and other infrastructure.

PVH designs and markets branded apparel. The company owns brand names such as Calvin Klein, Tommy Hilfiger, and Van Heusen, and licenses other brands such as Speedo, Geoffrey Beene, and Kenneth Cole New York.

Pactiv produces packaging products such as waste bags, food storage bags, and disposable tableware and cookware sold primarily in North America under trademarks such as Hefty, as well as foodservice packaging.
PTC develops software for computer-aided design and product lifecycle management.

Phillips 66 transports and processes natural gas, liquids, and crude oil in the U.S. The company refines crude oil and manufactures and markets petrochemicals and plastics, as well as refined petroleum products, mainly in the U.S. and Europe.
Public Storage is a REIT that owns and operates self-storage facilities which offer storage for lease on a month-to-month basis, for personal and business use.
Prudential offers a wide array of financial products and services, including life insurance, annuities, retirement-related services, mutual funds and investment management.

Perrigo is a global over-the-counter pharmaceutical and consumer goods company. The company makes infant formulas for the store brand market, provides generic topical prescription products, and receives royalties from sales of the multiple sclerosis drug, Tysabri.

PPL is a utility holding company that delivers electricity to customers in the U.K., Pennsylvania, Kentucky, Virginia and Tennessee; delivers natural gas to customers in Kentucky; and generates electricity from power plants in Kentucky.
